Φ(Universe 25) = σ(abundance|collapse) ∘ ρ(social_hierarchy|behavioral_sink) ∘ λ(utopia|dystopia) ∘ β(population_growth|reproductive_failure) ∘ δγ(rise|extinction) ∘ μ(designed_paradise|structural_decay) + ε | :terminal_decline

## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: abundance|collapse — Distinguishes between unlimited material resources and the social collapse they paradoxically produce when meaning structures fail.
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: social_hierarchy|behavioral_sink — Maps the relational breakdown from hierarchy to behavioral pathology, including aggression, withdrawal, and disengagement.
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: utopia|dystopia — The engineered paradise transforms into its opposite through the erosion of social roles, mating behaviors, and parental care.
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: population_growth|reproductive_failure — The growth curve peaks and inverts as behavioral pathology leads to 100% juvenile mortality and zero reproduction.
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: rise|extinction — The full cycle from colonization through population peak to terminal decline, repeated 25+ times with identical outcomes.
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: designed_paradise|structural_decay — The physical structure of the mouse utopia cannot compensate for the decay of social structure.

## Z-State
:terminal_decline — The irreversible point beyond which no intervention can restore population viability.

## Tendency
δγ → 0.85

